-- Coal of Africa to Pay $75 Million for Chapudi Coal Project in South Africa
-- B y   V i c t o r i a   B a t c h e l o r
-- 2010-11-28T22:31:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-28/coal-of-africa-to-pay-75-million-for-south-africa-coal-assets.html
Coal of Africa Ltd. has entered into
an agreement to pay $75 million to buy the Chapudi Coal Project
and related exploration properties in the Limpopo Province of
South Africa, from joint venture companies held by Rio Tinto
Minerals Development Ltd. and Kwezi Mining (Proprietary) Ltd.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Victoria Batchelor at 
 vbatchelor@bloomberg.net  